A Bubbling Hotspring~
   It is dangerously hot here at the source of the Phoenix Feather Hot Springs.
Still, from time to time the brave, foolish, or pyromantic guests decide they
want to experience the pinnacle of heat.  For them, the resort has formed the
hot spring into a cozy little pool.  A great cloud of steam rises up as the
scalding water touches the chill air, covering the nearby walls of the resort
with condensation that sometimes turns to ice and sometimes simply falls back
into the pool.  A stone shelf on the north wall, which is the south wall of the
resort, holds a pitcher of drinking water so that foolish patrons don't get
dehydrated and pass out.  After a guest has reached their limit, they may
retreat into the main pool down the cascade to the south.    
